full_text:
I love Rang so much and it pains me to see what the writer did to him.

He, like Yeon, Ji A, Yu Ri, Soo Ho, Shin Ju, Granny, her husband, Ji A's friends and the snail bride also deserved a happy ending, not to be placed in the same category as imoogi.

Thats all i'm gonna say.
full_text(utf-8):
b"I love Rang so much and it pains me to see what the writer did to him.

He, like Yeon, Ji A, Yu Ri, Soo Ho, Shin Ju, Granny, her husband, Ji A's friends and the snail bride also deserved a happy ending, not to be placed in the same category as imoogi.

Thats all i'm gonna say."

full_text: Lastly, it's about time writers learn that redemption doesn't equal as death, even less when the character receiving that tragic outcome already had the redemption arc completed, like in this case.
full_text(utf-8): b"Lastly, it's about time writers learn that redemption doesn't equal as death, even less when the character receiving that tragic outcome already had the redemption arc completed, like in this case."

full_text:
I completely oppose Rang's death, i'm super devastated cause he also had the right to be happy and live a new life.
But he was treated like a scapegoat, which makes this even more heartbreaking and wrong.
full_text(utf-8): b"I completely oppose Rang's death, i'm super devastated cause he also had the right to be happy and live a new life.\nBut he was treated like a scapegoat, which makes this even more heartbreaking and wrong."

full_text:
His death could have been avoided, his death wasn't necessary at all.
What the writer did to him was unjustified and undeserving, Rang deserved so much better than this.
Also, how could you deny Yeon of his only brother and family?? That's too much.
full_text(utf-8): b"His death could have been avoided, his death wasn't necessary at all.\nWhat the writer did to him was unjustified and undeserving, Rang deserved so much better than this.\nAlso, how could you deny Yeon of his only brother and family?? That's too much."

full_text:
Denying him his only wish before dying was even worse, he couldn't even have that little happiness before his last breath??
Do you think that's right?? He was the only one meeting a tragic outcome whe all the rest got their happy ending.
full_text(utf-8): b"Denying him his only wish before dying was even worse, he couldn't even have that little happiness before his last breath??\nDo you think that's right?? He was the only one meeting a tragic outcome whe all the rest got their happy ending."

full_text: Rang was given a huge development, he changed to be a better person, he helped others, he deserved to be given a second chance in life, he deserved to have a little happiness. But by killing him at the end precisely because he was starting to be happy, it's a super low move.
full_text(utf-8): b"Rang was given a huge development, he changed to be a better person, he helped others, he deserved to be given a second chance in life, he deserved to have a little happiness. But by killing him at the end precisely because he was starting to be happy, it's a super low move."

full_text: There's countless of ways to make people atonish for their crimes, Rang already cleaned himself enough, but even if he needed to do more, I can give you a full list of suggestions and ideas to do so.
full_text(utf-8): b"There's countless of ways to make people atonish for their crimes, Rang already cleaned himself enough, but even if he needed to do more, I can give you a full list of suggestions and ideas to do so."

full_text:
Rang wronged people, he commited crimes, but he didn't deserve to die like he did.
He already compensated enough by joinning Yeon, saving countless of lives and being the one giving the last punch to the imoogi, he already had his redemption.
full_text(utf-8): b"Rang wronged people, he commited crimes, but he didn't deserve to die like he did.\nHe already compensated enough by joinning Yeon, saving countless of lives and being the one giving the last punch to the imoogi, he already had his redemption."

full_text: It's already awful enough to kill him just because he was managing to be happy, but on top of that, you have to make him perish in front of the people he loves the most without being able to say goodbye to them when he was so desperately trying to do so before his last moments.
full_text(utf-8): b"It's already awful enough to kill him just because he was managing to be happy, but on top of that, you have to make him perish in front of the people he loves the most without being able to say goodbye to them when he was so desperately trying to do so before his last moments."

full_text:
Now you tell me, is that fair?????
Is it okay to even deny him that simple and pure last wish??
full_text(utf-8): b'Now you tell me, is that fair?????\nIs it okay to even deny him that simple and pure last wish??'

full_text: Cause he vanished before Yu Ri, Soo Ho and Shin Ju reached him, all he could do was give one last smile to them while crying, knowing that he couldn't say everything he wanted to say to them, knowing that he failed to fulfill his last wish, when he was so close of it.
full_text(utf-8): b"Cause he vanished before Yu Ri, Soo Ho and Shin Ju reached him, all he could do was give one last smile to them while crying, knowing that he couldn't say everything he wanted to say to them, knowing that he failed to fulfill his last wish, when he was so close of it."

full_text: At the end, all he could see is them running towards him desperately but failing to reach him, he wanted to say farewell, he wanted to say goodbye, but he wasn't even allowed to have that one thing.
full_text(utf-8): b"At the end, all he could see is them running towards him desperately but failing to reach him, he wanted to say farewell, he wanted to say goodbye, but he wasn't even allowed to have that one thing."

full_text: He desperately told to Ji A to please call them over cause he truly wanted to see them and talk to them one last time, he even kept checking the time on his phone and looking around while looking for them, you can't imagine how much that broke my heart.
full_text(utf-8): b"He desperately told to Ji A to please call them over cause he truly wanted to see them and talk to them one last time, he even kept checking the time on his phone and looking around while looking for them, you can't imagine how much that broke my heart."

full_text: The worst is that he wasn't even allowed to fulfill his one and only last wish, which was saying goodbye to his loved ones, Yu Ri, Soo Ho and Shin Ju.
full_text(utf-8): b"The worst is that he wasn't even allowed to fulfill his one and only last wish, which was saying goodbye to his loved ones, Yu Ri, Soo Ho and Shin Ju."

full_text:
Rang was truly chosen to be the one sacrificing because he finally cherished his life and had a family, how cruel is that??

It's like saying to his face: "Hey, since you're the happiest right now, you gotta be the one dying. Sorry not sorry."

I'm sorry, but that's awful.
